news.title: ICICI Home Finance directed to pay Rs 25,000 for not processing loan application for three years
news.para: R Murugesan, 46, of Kothur near VG Patty in the district, who was working in Mysuru, approached ICICI Home Finance’s Mysuru branch in January 2019 seeking a housing loan. Murugesan paid Rs 3,540 towards the processing fee. He submitted the required documents.

news.title: China REITs plumb record lows as economic gloom lingers
news.para: Chinese real estate investment trusts (REITs), which issue shares to investors against a portfolio of real estate holdings, have hit successive lows in the first few days of 2024.

news.title: Delhi: Bhuvan Bam buys Greater Kailash property for Rs 11 crore
news.para: The 180 sq metre bungalow is near to the previous home of Bam family and he has paid Rs 77 lakh stamps duty for the transaction.

news.title: MahaRERA reports 3,927 projects completion in 2023; highest since authority established
news.para: In 2023, a record-breaking 3,927 housing projects were successfully completed, showcasing a remarkable improvement from the previous year's count of 1,749 completed projects.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: VMRDA is spending Rs 660 crore on reconstituted layouts for 2,000 farmers
news.para: In these 83 layouts, spanning 4,828 acres, nearly 1.42 lakh homeless people have been allocated one cent each. The land was pooled from farmers in various mandals of the district.

news.title: Is it mandatory to purchase home insurance against home loans?
news.para: Currently, in India, purchasing home insurance is not mandatory to get a home loan sanctioned. A financial institution cannot force you to invest in one. However, getting home loan insurance is a good idea as it protects your finances and covers home loan amounts in case of mishaps.

news.title: Land-for-land policy banned; 'scam' by Jaipur development body to be probed
news.para: A section of Jaipur Development Authority (JDA) officials is reportedly involved in the scam, which pertains to prime government land having been handed over to developers and brokers.

news.title: Gurugram civic body to seal, auction properties of top tax defaulters
news.para: An senior official said that a list of top defaulters was already prepared since they were issued notices and the civic body will soon initiate the process to take action against them.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body seals around 70 illegal buildings in different areas of the city
news.para: These buildings included commercial buildings, industrial units, labour quarters, etc. The buildings have been established in violation of the building bylaws.

news.title: Belagavi: Buda starts marking boundaries for residential project at Kanabargi
news.para: The scheme is being developed on 160 acres in Kanabargi area. The Buda is implementing a residential scheme after almost 11 years.

news.title: Haryana RERA advises buyer to not invest in projects without RERA registration
news.para: "If any person is facilitating sale purchase in unregistered projects through advertisement or by any other means that is a violation of the Act," said the authority.

news.title: Creditors vote to liquidate Gayatri Projects after rejecting sole bid
news.para: Mark AB was offering a total of ₹650 crore, of which only ₹50 crore was upfront cash, ET had reported in October. It was the only serious offer lenders had received, which has now been rejected because of its low value.

news.title: Gurugram: Illegal buildings come up again on land off Golf Course Road, town planner seals six plots
news.para: Following online dispute and multiple allotment of plots in the residential society, government had out a complete ban on construction in the colony.

news.title: Gurugram: Adani Oyster Grande owners protest outside builder's office
news.para: Residents alleged that the developer is trying to hand over common assets and funds to RWA, which does not represent them, despite the matter pending before registrar general of societies.

news.title: Over two decades delay by builder sounded death knell for SRA project: Bombay HC
news.para: Justice Milind Jadhav on Tuesday dismissed the petition of Surjit Singh Arora of Arora Builders and directed him to pay Rs 50,000 cost to Kirtikar Libr-ary in HC within two weeks.

news.title: Sebi moots additional proposals on REITS, InvITs issuing subordinate units
news.para: ​Sebi, in a consultation paper issued on Wednesday, has also made suggestions related to changes in terms and conditions of the subordinate units by the Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITs) or Infrastructure Investment Trusts (InvITs) post-issuance.

news.title: NCLAT rejects Union Bank's plea to oppose Darwin Platform Group's bid for Lavasa Corp
news.para: ​Union Bank of India (UBI) had challenged the July 21, 2023, order of the Mumbai bench of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT), which approved the resolution plan of Darwin Platform Infrastructure Ltd for Lavasa Corporation that was developing a private hill city in the Pune district.

news.title: Nuvama, Cushman form JV to launch Rs 3,000 crore commercial realty fund
news.para: The joint venture aims to empower investors with superior fund management expertise through Nuvama, while leveraging Cushman's global expertise in the commercial real estate industry, the companies said.

news.title: Skanska flags $195 million impairment charge in Q4 2023
news.para: Heavily indebted property developers in Skanska's home market Sweden have faced growing problems and while a plunge in the housing market there has leveled out, construction activity related to both sectors has tumbled.

news.title: Supertech chairman seeks interim bail in money laundering case on medical grounds
news.para: Arora told Additional Sessions Judge Devender Kumar Jangala he has lost around 10 kg since his arrest and required "urgent medical assistance".
